; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures timer2 and generates a periodic interrupt based on external clock source.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting target port with a suitable instrument.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. Timer2
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. Timer14 : PB2/PB2 (Output/Capture Input)
;               : PB2 (External Clock Input)
;    2. Timer21 : PC6/PC6 (Output/Capture Input)
;               : PC11 (External Clock Input)
;
; E. Port Connection
;    1. PB2 (Timer14 Output) ----> PC11 (Timer21 External Clock Input)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; Timer21
; 1. Channel                   : 1 (Timer21)
;
; 2. Clock                     : [ 1 e f 0 ]
;    Source                    : e (External Clock Input) 
;    External Clock Input Edge : f (Falling) 
;    Timer2 Pre-Divide         : 0 (No Pre-Divider available so default 0)
;
; 3. Config                    : [ 1 i p h 0 0 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : p (Periodic)
;    Output Port Polarity      : h (High)
;    A Data                    : 0
;    B Data                    : 0
;
; Timer14
; 1. Channel                   : 4 (Timer14)
;
; 2. Clock                     : [ 4 p 3999 ]
;    Source                    : p (PCLK)
;    Timer1 Pre-Divide         : 3999 (Pre-Divide + 1)
;
; 3. Config                    : [ 4 i p h 5000 5000 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : p (Period)
;    Output Port Polarity      : h (High)
;    A Data                    : 5000
;    B Data                    : 5000
;
; PCU
; 1. Port Group                : 1/2 (PCU Port B/C)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 1 2 a 0 ] [ 2 11 a 4 ]
;    Pin Number                : 2 / 11
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 0 (T14OUT) / 4 (EC21)
;
; PCU (PB2)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 1 2 a 0'
mpause 30

; PCU(PC11)
sendln 'port 2 11 a 4'
mpause 30

; Timer14
sendln 'cm timer1'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 4'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 4'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 4 p 3999'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 4 i p h 5000 5000'
mpause 30
sendln 'log off'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 4'
mpause 30

; Timer21
sendln 'cm timer2'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 1 e f 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 1 i p h 0 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'log on'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 1'
